C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarth%20was%20born%20about%20four%20and%20a%20half%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20alongside%20several%20sibling%20planets%2C%20all%20of%20them%20formed%20from%20fragments%20of%20material%20left%20over%20after%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20Sun.%20It%20began%20as%20a%20glob%20of%20fiery%2C%20fluid%20rock%20spinning%20amidst%20other%20bits%20of%20ice%20and%20stone.%20But%20over%20the%20course%20of%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20first%20half%20billion%20years%2C%20its%20molten%20surface%20cooled%20and%20solidified%3B%20its%20dry%2C%20sulfurous%20skies%20became%20unending%20showers%20of%20acid%20rain%3B%20its%20empty%20basins%20filled%20with%20water.%20In%20these%20new%20oceans%20simmered%20a%20rich%20elemental%20brew%20of%20carbon%2C%20hydrogen%2C%20nitrogen%2C%20phosphorous%2C%20iron%E2%80%94to%20mention%20but%20a%20few%20star%20ingredients%E2%80%94absorbing%20heat-energy%20from%20deep-sea%20hydrothermal%20vents%20and%20joining%20together%20into%20chains%20of%20chemicals.%20These%20complex%20molecules%20then%20clustered%20together%2C%20generating%20higher%20order%20structures%2C%20eventually%20forming%20cells%20that%20ate%20and%20breathed%20and%20reproduced%E2%80%94living%20avatars%20of%20dust%2C%20born%20of%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20own%20dynamically%20interconnected%20biological%2C%20geological%2C%20and%20chemical%20processes%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Ebiogeochemistry%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20earliest%20lifeforms%20were%20coming%20into%20being%2C%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20surface%20was%20still%20being%20relentlessly%20pummelled%20by%20meteors%2C%20some%20of%20them%20the%20size%20of%20mountains.%20Great%20impacts%20injected%20new%20material%20into%20our%20planet%2C%20cracking%20and%20reshaping%20its%20biogeochemistry.%20In%20this%20environment%2C%20about%203.5%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20some%20of%20those%20early%20cells%20evolved%20a%20new%20ability%20to%20convert%20light-energy%20from%20the%20sun%20into%20chemical%20fuel%20through%20a%20process%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ephotosynthesis%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20takes%20carbon-dioxide%20from%20the%20air%20and%20emits%20oxygen%20as%20metabolic%20waste.%20By%20two%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20buildup%20of%20oxygen%20was%20turning%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20skies%20blue%20above%20its%20oceans%20of%20rust-red.%20Many%20forms%20of%20life%20in%20that%20nascent%20biosphere%20were%20poisoned%20by%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslate.com%2Ftechnology%2F2014%2F07%2Fthe-great-oxygenation-event-the-earths-first-mass-extinction.html%5C%22%3Eatmospheric%20oxygen%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20went%20extinct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3ECoal%20beds%20found%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mlsu.ac.in%2Fecontents%2F1895_Distribution%252520of%252520Coal%252520%26amp%3B%252520Petroleum%252520in%252520India.pdf%5C%22%3Epeninsular%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20the%20remains%20of%20swamp%20forests%20that%20bloomed%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffossil.energy.gov%2Finternational%2FPublications%2Fucg_1106_gsi.pdf%5C%22%3E290%20million%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20supercontinent%20Pangea%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2F38218-facts-about-pangaea.html%5C%22%3Ein%20extreme%20southern%20latitudes%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20Earth%20was%20so%20hot%20that%20forests%20bloomed%20near%20Antarctica.%20But%20170%20million%20years%20later%2C%20the%20land%20containing%20those%20primeval%20forests%E2%80%94long%20since%20dead%20and%20buried%E2%80%94broke%20off%20as%20an%20island%20and%20floated%20northward.%20Its%20collision%20with%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass%20pushed%20up%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20highest%20mountains%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DA_K6LSSZ_34%5C%22%3Einducing%20the%20Indian%20monsoon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20planet-wide%20cooling%20trend.%20Sixty%20million%20years%20later%2C%20the%20country%20south%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20would%20find%20itself%20rich%20with%20coal.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20life%20itself%20was%20not%20defeated.%20The%20cells%20that%20did%20survive%20continued%20to%20diversify%20into%20myriad%20new%20forms%20that%20could%20withstand%20and%20even%20make%20use%20of%20this%20corrosive%20new%20gas.%20Some%20of%20these%20found%20ways%20to%20work%20together%2C%20joining%20into%20multicellular%20lifeforms%2C%20mixing%20genes%20through%20sexual%20reproduction%2C%20eventually%20filling%20the%20oceans%20with%20early%20forms%20of%20fungi%2C%20plants%2C%20and%20animals%20by%20around%20one%20billion%20years%20ago.%20These%20creatures%20grew%20and%20died%2C%20burrowed%20and%20crawled%2C%20built%20residual%20structures%2C%20stirred%20sediments%2C%20altered%20rocks%20and%20seabeds%20in%20ways%20that%20further%20changed%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20biogeochemistry.%20This%20changing%20geochemistry%20also%20affected%20the%20structure%20and%20motion%20of%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20crust%2C%20now%20sliding%20and%20tearing%2C%20bumping%20and%20churning%20up%20the%20landforms%20into%20barren%20mountains%20and%20valleys%20and%20volcanic%20alleys%2C%20exposing%20new%2C%20unweathered%20rock%E2%80%94which%20further%20changed%20biogeochemical%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20this%20lively%20flourishing%2C%20the%20changes%20led%20to%20the%20entire%20planet%20freezing%20over.%20By%20around%20720%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20floating%20icebergs%20and%20islands%20of%20slush%20were%20drifting%20over%20the%20tropical%20seas%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DVaaSoEsrtkk%5C%22%3Esnowball%20Earth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20planet%20lay%20cocooned%20within%20vast%20sheets%20of%20ice.%20In%20the%20stagnant%2C%20anoxic%20waters%20beneath%2C%20life%20barely%20carried%20on%E2%80%94but%20it%20%3Cem%3Edid%3C%2Fem%3E%20carry%20on.%20And%20after%20the%20ice%20truly%20loosened%20its%20grip%2C%20about%20630%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20