nd%20shrinking%20islands%2C%20even%20as%20the%20planet%20rebounded%20again%20and%20again%20between%20different%20climatic%20states.%20Global%20average%20temperatures%20sometimes%20rose%20or%20fell%20by%20several%20degrees%E2%80%94magnitudes%20that%20dwarf%20the%20climate%20change%20already%20threatening%20modern%20human%20civilization.%20But%20such%20shifts%20took%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20far%20slower%20than%20the%20changes%20we%E2%80%99re%20observing%20today.%20Sometimes%20extreme%20changes%20in%20climate%20and%20biogeochemistry%20triggered%20global%20mass%20extinction%20events%2C%20when%20more%20than%20half%20of%20all%20known%20extant%20lifeforms%20were%20wiped%20out.%20Still%2C%20whenever%20the%20oceans%20were%20warm%E2%80%94and%20most%20of%20the%20past%20half%20a%20billion%20years%20have%20been%20%3Cem%3Every%3C%2Fem%3E%20warm%E2%80%94algae%20and%20phytoplankton%20proliferated%20in%20tremendous%20blooms%2C%20billions%20of%20photosynthesizing%20cells%2C%20reproducing%20and%20dying%20with%20vigorous%20rampancy%3B%20copious%20quantities%20of%20their%20remains%20piled%20up%20on%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20four-hundred%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20forested%20swamplands%20had%20grown%20across%20large%20parts%20of%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20landmasses.%20Great%2C%20primeval%20trees%20sucked%20the%20abundant%20carbon-dioxide%20from%20the%20sky%20and%20used%20the%20carbon%20to%20build%20their%20trunks%E2%80%94another%20novel%20biochemistry%3A%20wood.%20When%20the%20trees%20died%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20quite%20rot%20away%2C%20for%20creatures%20fully%20able%20to%20digest%20wood%20had%20not%20yet%20evolved.%20Instead%2C%20the%20woody%20plants%20fell%20into%20heaps%20that%20sunk%20slowly%20into%20the%20mud.%20Folded%20deep%20into%20the%20ground%2C%20the%20detritus%20of%20those%20first%20trees%20and%20all%20those%20algae%20and%20plankton%20were%20pressed%20over%20many%20millions%20of%20years%20into%20beds%20of%20new%2C%20carbon-dense%20miner