nuary-alone-60-in-the-value-of-rs-1-crore%5C%22%3Eas%20recently%20as%20January%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hundreds%20of%20crores%20worth%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20sold%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20who%20benefitted%20from%20this%20scheme%2C%20and%20from%20the%20delayed%20decision%20from%20the%20court%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20including%20the%20latest%20tranche%2C%20Rs%2016%2C518.11%20crore%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20been%20sold%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20505px)%2085vw%2C%20505px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22505%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline-300x292.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15123947%2FEBs_till_Jan24_Timeline-1024x995.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697263%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22491%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20the%20BJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Congress%20has%20received%20just%209.5%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20at%20Rs%201%2C135%20crore.%20The%20Trinamool%20Congress%20has%20received%20Rs%201%2C096%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20this%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20in%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-admin%2Fpost-new.php%5C%22%3E%20The%20Hindu%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20pointed%20out%20that%20as%20much%20as%2054%25%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20total%20income%20in%20the%20year%202022-23%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20a%20whopping%20Rs%202%2C120.06%20crore.%20During%20the%20six-year%20period%20between%202018%20and%202023%2C%20more%20than%2052%25%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20total%20donations%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%205271.9751%20crore%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FAnalysis_of_Donations_to_Registered_Recognised_Political_Parties_FY_2016-17_to_2021-22.pdf%5C%22%3EAssociation%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20earned%20Rs%20171%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegional%20parties%20too%20have%20received%20large%20sums%20of%20money%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20The%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Ffive-regional-parties-together-got-over-rs-1200-crore-in-electoral-bonds-in-2022-23%2Farticleshow%2F106032800.cms%5C%22%3Ethe%20biggest%20recipient%20among%20them%20in%202022-23%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20receiving%20Rs%20529%20crore%20through%20this%20method.%20The%20TMC%20came%20in%20second%2C%20with%20Rs%20329%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20BJD%20with%20Rs%20152%20crore%20and%20YSR%20Congress%20with%20Rs%2052%20crore.%20Four%20of%20these%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20excluding%20the%20BRS%20%E2%80%93%20had%20received%20larger%20sums%20of%20money%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20in%202021-22%3A%20Rs%20528%20crore%20for%20the%20TMC%2C%20Rs%20306%20crore%20for%20the%20DMK%2C%20Rs%20291%20crore%20for%20the%20BJD%20and%20Rs%2060%20crore%20for%20the%20YSR%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20general%20election%20before%20which%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20sold%20%E2%80%93%20was%20the%20most%20expensive%20election%20the%20world%20had%20ever%20seen%20until%20that%20point%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-06-03%2Findia-s-bitterly-fought-poll-becomes-the-world-s-most-expensive%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20About%20%248.7%20billion%20was%20spent%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20more%20than%20double%20of%20what%20was%20spent%20for%20the%202014%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20they%20were%20first%20introduced%2C%20transparency%20rights%20activists%20have%20raised%20serious%20questions%20over%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20and%20also%20about%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it%20was%20brought%20in%2C%20including%20ignoring%20the%20concerns%20raised%20by%20the%20then%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20governor%20and%20without%20holding%20any%20sort%20of%20public%20consultation.%20Legal%20challenges%20to%20the%20law%20were%20filed%20almost%20immediately%20in%20the%20courts%2C%20saying%20this%20scheme%20threatened%20democracy%20by%20allowing%20anonymous%20donations%20and%20encouraging%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20relationship%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20big%20business.%20Now%2C%20nearly%20seven%20years%20later%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20validated%20all%20those%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20ordered%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20release%20details%20of%20all%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20%E2%80%93%20thus%20removing%20the%20veil%20of%20secrecy%20over%20those%20who%20have%20donated%20hundreds%20of%20crores%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20parties.%20That%20money%2C%20however%2C%20has%20now%20already%20funded%20two%20general%20election%20cycles%20and%20multiple%20state%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707982339000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F14185439%2Fcoins-gebbaa9855_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Money%20that%20exchanged%20hands%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20has%20already%20funded%20two%20general%20election%20cycles%20and%20multiple%20state%20elections.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Democracy%20slides%20amid%20wars%2C%20political%20polarisation%3A%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707982198000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107715517%2Cimgsize-1099785.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fdemocracy-slides-amid-wars-political-polarisation-study%2Farticleshow%2F107714938.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107714938.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDemocratic%20standards%20across%20the%20world%20fell%20in%202023%20amid%20the%20spread%20of%20wars%2C%20authoritarian%20crackdowns%20and%20declining%20levels%20of%20trust%20in%20mainstream%20political%20parties%2C%20the%20Economist%20Intelligence%20Unit%20(EIU)%20said%20on%20Thursday.%20%26quot%3BMore%20countries%20are%20experiencing%20declining%20levels%20of%20trust%20in%20mainstream%20political%20parties%20and%20leaders%2C%20and%20succumbing%20to%20'culture%20wars'%20of%20the%20sort%20that%20have%20long%20characterised%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fdemocracy-slides-amid-wars-political-polarisation-study%2Farticleshow%2F107714938.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fdemocracy-slides-amid-wars-political-polarisation-study%2Famp_articleshow%2F107714938.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fdemocracy-slides-amid-wars-political-polarisation-study%2Famp_articleshow%2F107714938.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20One%20Initiative%20is%20Taking%20Paediatric%20Cancer%20Care%20To%20The%20Doorsteps%20of%202500%20Kids%20in%20Rural%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20sponsored%20by%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildhood%20cancers%20are%20a%20rising%20problem%20globally.%20The%20WHO%20states%20that%20over%20four%20lakh%20children%20develop%20cancer%20each%20year%2C%20with%20India%20accounting%20for%2050%2C000%20of%20these%20cases.%20While%20survival%20rates%20are%20high%20in%20high-income%20countries%2C%20India%20still%20faces%20the%20problems%20of%20lack%20of%20diagnosis%2C%20delayed%20diagnosis%2C%20access%20to%20care%2C%20and%20continuation%20of%20treatment.%20An%20ICMR%20(Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research)%20paper%20states%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20specific%20policy%20work%20to%20bring%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F333669%2Fbasic-health-tests-we-should-do-regularly-heart-lungs-kidneys-cancer-detection-inspiring-story%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20childhood%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20control%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20an%20ICMR-NCDIR%20(National%20Centre%20for%20Disease%20Informatics%20and%20Research)%20study%20found%20that%20a%20dedicated%20paediatric%20oncology%20department%20was%20available%20in%2041.6%25%20of%20government%20hospitals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20instance%2C%2010-year-old%20Saksham%20(name%20changed).%20Residing%20in%20Timbi%20village%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20playful%20child%20started%20experiencing%20unexplained%20fatigue%2C%20frequent%20infections%2C%20and%20fever%20in%202022.%20His%20father%2C%20Ramesh%20(name%20changed)%2C%20a%20farmer%2C%20consulted%20local%20doctors%20(for%20which%20he%20had%20to%20travel%2020%20km)%2C%20but%20none%20of%20the%20medications%20they%20gave%20worked%20on%20the%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaksham%20was%20then%20taken%20almost%2090%20km%20away%2C%20to%20%E2%80%98The%20Himalayan%20Hospital%E2%80%99%20in%20Dehradun%2C%20where%20blood%20tests%20revealed%20that%20he%20had%20Acute%20Lymphoblastic%20Leukaemia%20(ALL)%2C%20a%20type%20of%20blood%20cancer.%20Father%20to%20six%20children%2C%20with%20barely%20any%20income%2C%20Ramesh%20had%20already%20spent%20about%20Rs%2050%2C000%20for%20his%20travels%20and%20different%20treatments.%20The%20treatment%20for%20ALL%2C%20doctors%20estimated%2C%20would%20be%20about%20Rs%208%20lakhs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20lost%20all%20hope.%20My%20income%20was%20just%20enough%20to%20feed%20my%20family.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20to%20do%20and%20how%20to%20save%20my%20child%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ramesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20then%20informed%20Ramesh%20about%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20which%20supports%20cancer%20treatment%20and%20bone%20marrow%20transplants.%20Working%20with%20the%20hospital%20and%20the%20family%2C%20the%20programme%20has%20covered%20the%20cost%20of%20chemotherapy%2C%20bone%20marrow%20transplant%2C%20blood%20transfusions%20and%20other%20medical%20expenses%20for%20Saksham%2C%20who%20is%20now%20on%20the%20road%20to%20recovery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20run%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20government%2C%20is%20bridging%20the%20gap%20of%20financial%20access%20for%20children%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20afford%20treatment%20for%20critical%20diseases%20like%20cancer.%20So%20far%2C%20over%202%2C500%20children%20have%20benefited%20from%20this%20initiative%20and%20have%20received%20life-saving%20treatments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHelping%20parents%20access%20quality%20cancer%20care%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20853px)%20100vw%2C%20853px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20government%2C%20is%20closing%20the%20financial%20gap%20for%20children%20unable%20to%20afford%20treatment%20for%20serious%20illnesses%20such%20as%20cancer.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361.jpg%20853w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-500x750.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-768x1152.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361-150x225.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341893%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Hans%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20Government%2C%20is%20closing%20the%20financial%20gap%20for%20children%20unable%20to%20afford%20treatment%20for%20serious%20illnesses%2C%20such%20as%20cancer.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablished%20in%202017%20in%20close%20partnership%20with%20the%20state%20government%2C%20the%20programme%20provides%20free%20treatment%20to%20children%20aged%200-18%20years%20who%20are%20suffering%20from%20critical%20diseases%20or%20conditions%2C%20complementing%20the%20Rashtriya%20Bal%20Swasthya%20Karyakram%20(RBSK)%20and%20subsequently%2C%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20schemes%20by%20supporting%20treatment%20for%20conditions%20outside%20the%20schemes%E2%80%99%20purview%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20District%20Early%20Intervention%20Centers%20(DEICs)%2C%20established%20under%20the%20RBSK%2C%20identify%20infants%20and%20children%20with%20developmental%20delays%2C%20disabilities%20and%20diseases.%20Once%20identified%2C%20these%20children%20are%20referred%20to%20two%20empanelled%20medical%20colleges%2C%20namely%20The%20Himalayan%20Hospital%20(Swami%20Ram%20Himalayan%20University)%20and%20Shri%20Mahant%20Indresh%20Hospital.%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%20has%20partnered%20with%20these%20two%20colleges%20and%20reimburses%20the%20treatment%20expenses%20for%20diseases%20like%20cancer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20programme%20is%20broadly%20designed%2C%2090%20percent%20of%20the%20patients%20who%20need%20support%20are%20cancer%20patients%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F322528%2Futtar-pradesh-cancer-survivor-sandeep-kumar-runs-digiswasthya-free-medical-teleconsultation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%20treatments%3C%2Fa%3E%20require%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20and%20money.%20The%20average%20cost%20of%20treating%20common%20cancers%20in%20children%20like%20ALL%20and%20Acute%20Myeloid%20Leukaemia%20(AML)%20can%20easily%20range%20from%20Rs%205-15%20lakhs%20or%20even%20more%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20disease%20at%20the%20time%20of%20diagnosis.%20Most%20of%20the%20children%20who%20come%20in%20for%20treatment%20are%20either%20infants%2C%20or%20between%20the%20age%20group%20of%205-8.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommon%20cancers%20in%20children%20are%20different%20from%20those%20seen%20in%20adults.%20Dr%20BP%20Kalra%2C%20Professor%20of%20Pediatrics%2C%20Department%20of%20Pediatrics%2C%20Himalayan%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%2C%20Dehradun%20states%20that%20leukaemias%20(cancer%20of%20blood-forming%20tissues)%2C%20lymphomas%20(cancer%20of%20the%20lymphatic%20system)%20are%20the%20most%20common%2C%20followed%20by%20brain%20and%20bone%20cancer%20and%20tumours%20like%20the%20Wilms%20Tumour%20(renal%20cancer).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20see%20that%20most%20commonly%2C%20children%20get%20cancer%20in%20the%20first%20or%20second%20year%20of%20life%2C%20or%20in%20the%205-10%20age%20group.%20In%20the%20school-going%20age%20group%2C%20leukaemias%20and%20lymphomas%20are%20most%20common.%20The%20outcome%20is%20generally%20good%20in%20this%20age%20group%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Kalra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Himalayan%20Institute%20caters%20to%20children%20from%20across%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20sometimes%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20more.%C2%A0%20The%20reason%2C%20the%20doctor%20adds%2C%20is%20because%20of%20lack%20of%20facilities%20for%20treatment%2C%20which%20makes%20parents%20and%20children%20travel%20far%20and%20wide%20for%20basic%20access.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20needed%20for%20good%20outcomes%2C%20according%20to%20Dr%20Kalra%2C%20is%20an%20early%2C%20prompt%2C%20correct%20diagnosis%20which%20should%20be%20followed%20by%20effective%2C%20evidence-based%20therapy%20after%20which%20supportive%20care%20is%20paramount.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHelping%202%2C500%20children%20get%20cancer%20treatment%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans2-1707980359.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Camps%20by%20the%20the%20District%20Early%20Intervention%20Centers%20(DEICs)%20identify%20infants%20and%20children%20with%20developmental%20delays%2C%20disabilities%20and%20diseases.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans2-1707980359.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans2-1707980359-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans2-1707980359-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans2-1707980359-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans2-1707980359-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341892%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ECamps%20by%20the%20District%20Early%20Intervention%20Centers%20(DEICs)%20identify%20infants%20and%20children%20with%20developmental%20delays%2C%20disabilities%20and%20diseases.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildhood%20cancer%20management%20in%20Low%20and%20Middle-Income%20Countries%20(LMICs)%2C%20including%20India%2C%20is%20characterised%20by%20delayed%20diagnosis%20and%20treatment%20initiation%2C%20inadequate%2Fincomplete%20treatment%20and%20low%20survival%20rate%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20in%20Indian%20Cancer%20Society.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20parents%20must%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20common%20symptoms%20and%20go%20to%20a%20doctor%20when%20they%20notice%20these%20including%3A%20recurrent%20fevers%2C%20loss%20of%20appetite%2C%20loss%20of%20weight%2C%20swelling%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20body%2C%20persistent%20pain%2C%20sudden%20tiredness%2C%20fatigue%2C%20headaches%2C%20any%20lumps%20or%20mass.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20first%20step%20where%20families%20notice%20symptoms%20and%20access%20care%2C%20the%20second%20step%20is%20clinical%20evaluation%20and%20diagnosis.%20Facilities%20like%20the%20DEIC%20should%20be%20able%20to%20help%20in%20this%20step.%20The%20last%20and%20most%20crucial%20step%20is%20accessibility%20to%20treatment.%20As%20the%20majority%20of%20public%20hospitals%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F303740%2Fresearcher-quits-job-to-build-non-invasve-device-to-detect-breast-cancer-thermalytix-niramai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaediatric%20oncology%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20parents%20either%20have%20to%20take%20them%20far%20to%20a%20government%20hospital%20that%20has%20the%20treatment%2C%20or%20go%20to%20a%20private%20hospital%20nearby.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20trusts%20like%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%20is%20very%20important%20in%20such%20cases%2C%20as%20they%20help%20families%20afford%20quality%20healthcare%20and%20save%20the%20lives%20of%20their%20children%20through%20timely%20treatment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Kalra%20says%20that%20his%20biggest%20request%20to%20parents%20is%20to%20continue%20treatment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CParents%20must%20remain%20hopeful%20and%20continue%20treatment.%20The%20results%20are%20good%20and%20most%20children%20do%20well%2C%20after%20early%20diagnosis.%20We%20are%20thankful%20to%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%20which%20makes%20it%20possible%20for%20so%20many%20children%20to%20access%20treatment%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Dr%20Kalra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hans%20Bal%20Arogya%20Karyakram%2C%20which%20has%20been%20working%20on%20ground%20since%202017%2C%20has%20helped%20over%202%2C518%20children.%20A%20medical%20audit%20found%20that%20the%20survival%20rates%20of%20children%20had%20improved%20by%20more%20than%2080%25%20post-intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20success%20of%20and%20the%20learnings%20from%20the%20programme%20in%20Uttarakhand%2C%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%20is%20now%20ready%20to%20expand%20its%20support%20to%20children%20suffering%20from%20cancer%20under%20its%20Hans%20Paediatric%20Care%20programme%20and%20extending%20services%20to%20RN%20Tagore%20Hospital%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20G%20Kuppuswamy%20Naidu%20Memorial%20Hospital%20in%20Coimbatore%2C%20Narayana%20Multispeciality%20Hospital%20in%20Howrah%20and%20SGVP%20Hospital%20in%20Ahmedabad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20goal%20is%20to%20make%20access%20to%20cancer%20treatment%20possible%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F341755%2Fcongenital-heart-disease-in-babies-treatment-surgery-provided-by-hans-foundation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren%20across%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20location.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20way%20out.%20The%20disease%20can%20happen%20to%20anyone.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20lose%20hope%20and%20have%20patience%20and%20faith%20in%20your%20doctor.%20Try%20the%20treatment%20and%20complete%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Kalra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3B%20All%20pictures%20courtesy%3A%20The%20Hans%20Foundation)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707982174000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FHans1-1707980361.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D341889%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Hans%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20Bal%20Aarogya%20Karyakram%20supports%20paediatric%20oncology%20care%20for%20children%20in%20Uttarakhand.%20It%20has%20provided%20a%20total%20financial%20aid%20of%20Rs%208.5%20crore%20to%20children%20from%20underprivileged%20backgrounds%20who%20need%20this%20life-saving%20treatment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F341889%2Fhans-foundation-bal-aarogya-karyakram-childhood-cancer-paediatric-oncology-leukaemia-lymphoma%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Let%20the%20winner%20win%E2%80